Question.Title: Active transformations in Informatica
Question.Description: Which all transformations are used by Informatica as active transformations for processing of data?

Answers.Description:
There are multiple transformations in Informatica that are considered active. A thumb rule for an active transformation is that it changes in the number of rows between input and output. 
Some of the commonly used active transformations are:
Router 
Lookup
Source qualifier
Filter
Aggregator
Union
Sorter

Feel free to reach out for more questions if you have.

Question.Title: What is the difference between int and int32.
